
LibraryHelper Methods:

    MAIN METHODS

        void mainMenu();
            Shows the initial options,
            Reads the user's option until a valid one is obtained,
            Calls the appropriate LibraryHelper method or finish the application.

        void listAll();
            Calls the Library method getAllBooks();
            Prints books information;


        void insertNewBook();
            Obtains valid information to Book's attributes using the LibraryHelper methods:
                                              readAValidTitleOrAuthor() and readAValidYear();
            Saves the new book calling the save() method from Library;
            Checks if savedBook returned by save() method is equals to bookToBeSaved,
                                           if not, delete the book saved incorrectly.


        findBookMenu();
        updateBook();
        deleteBook();






    INSERT AUXILIARY METHODS
        String readAValidTitleOrAuthor(stringField field);
            reads the user's input until a valid String is obtained and returns it;
            uses the LibraryHelper validateTitleAndAuthorString() method to check the user's input;
            when the input is invalid, call the LibraryHelper method readAValidFailedOperationMenuOption() is called
                                                                                        to offer choices to the user

        int readAValidYear()
            reads the user's input until a valid year is obtained and returns it;
                        uses the LibraryHelper validateYear() method to check the user's input;
                        when the input is invalid, call the LibraryHelper method readAValidFailedOperationMenuOption() is called
                                                                                                    to offer choices to the user








    VALIDATIONS METHODS
        boolean validateTitleAndAuthorString(String inputtedString);
        int validateYear(String inputtedYear);
        char readAValidFailedOperationMenuOption();





    UTIL
        void showFailedOperationMenu(String failedOpertion);
        void printOutput(String output);
        void printOutput(String output, List<Book> books);
        void printInputAsk(String field);
        void printInvalidOption();
